{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2016}} [[File:Febo Conti 1.jpg|thumbnail|Febo Conti]] '''Febo Conti''' (25 December 1926 – 16 December 2012) was an Italian TV and radio presenter and actor.
Born in [[Bresso]], Conti started his career as radio-host in [[Radio Italia Nord]], and then in [[Radiotelevisione svizzera di lingua italiana|RTSI]].<ref name="vfg">{{cite news|title=Morto Febo Conti, pioniere della tv|url=http://brescia.corriere.it/brescia/notizie/cronaca/12_dicembre_17/febo-conti-morto-2113193807415.shtml|accessdate=18 December 2012|newspaper=[[Corriere Della Sera]]|date=18 December 2012}}</ref> He was best known as host of the [[RAI TV]] [[quiz show]] ''Chissà chi lo sa?'' (trad. "''Who knows, who knows?''") that put in front two teams of students from different schools with an encyclopedia as the prize. The show was a huge success and it was broadcast for thirteen years.<ref name=bio>{{cite news|last=Marco Molendini|title=Febo Conti è morto, volto storico della tv|url=http://www.ilmessaggero.it/spettacoli/televisione/morto_febo_conti_volto_storico_della_tv/notizie/238977.shtml|accessdate=18 December 2012|newspaper=[[Il Messaggero]]|date=18 December 2012}}</ref> Conti was also co-founder and, between 1975 and 1980, manager of the theme park [[Gardaland]].<ref name="vfg"/>
